From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0002/N] platform.m4: accept CHERI/Morello purecap pointer size

On Morello purecap, sizeof(int*)==16 (128-bit capability) while the
target CPU is aarch64 (OPENJDK_TARGET_CPU_BITS=64). OpenJDK's autoconf
treats this as a fatal mismatch. Add a single-arm exemption for the
aarch64+128bit case; every other mismatch still errors.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §5

--- a/make/autoconf/platform.m4
+++ b/make/autoconf/platform.m4
@@ -704,12 +704,19 @@ AC_DEFUN_ONCE([PLATFORM_SETUP_TARGET_CPU_BITS],
     TESTED_TARGET_CPU_BITS=`expr 8 \* $ac_cv_sizeof_int_p`

     if test "x$TESTED_TARGET_CPU_BITS" != "x$OPENJDK_TARGET_CPU_BITS"; then
-      AC_MSG_NOTICE([The tested number of bits in the target ($TESTED_TARGET_CPU_BITS) differs from the number of bits expected to be found in the target ($OPENJDK_TARGET_CPU_BITS)])
-      if test "x$COMPILE_TYPE" = xreduced; then
-        HELP_MSG_MISSING_DEPENDENCY([reduced])
-        AC_MSG_NOTICE([You are doing a reduced build. Check that you have 32-bit libraries installed. $HELP_MSG])
-      elif test "x$COMPILE_TYPE" = xcross; then
-        AC_MSG_NOTICE([You are doing a cross-compilation. Check that you have all target platform libraries installed.])
+      # stopless-java-gc: on CHERI/Morello purecap, pointers are 128-bit
+      # capabilities even though the target CPU is aarch64-64. Accept that
+      # case; everything else is still an error.
+      if test "x$OPENJDK_TARGET_CPU" = xaarch64 -a "x$TESTED_TARGET_CPU_BITS" = x128; then
+        AC_MSG_NOTICE([Detected CHERI/Morello purecap (128-bit pointers on 64-bit CPU); accepting.])
+      else
+        AC_MSG_NOTICE([The tested number of bits in the target ($TESTED_TARGET_CPU_BITS) differs from the number of bits expected to be found in the target ($OPENJDK_TARGET_CPU_BITS)])
+        if test "x$COMPILE_TYPE" = xreduced; then
+          HELP_MSG_MISSING_DEPENDENCY([reduced])
+          AC_MSG_NOTICE([You are doing a reduced build. Check that you have 32-bit libraries installed. $HELP_MSG])
+        elif test "x$COMPILE_TYPE" = xcross; then
+          AC_MSG_NOTICE([You are doing a cross-compilation. Check that you have all target platform libraries installed.])
+        fi
+        AC_MSG_ERROR([Cannot continue.])
       fi
-      AC_MSG_ERROR([Cannot continue.])
     fi
   fi
